Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @ginger{1%thumb-sized piece}. Peel the @sweet potato{1}, then chop into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the ginger, @Sri Lankan style curry powder{1%tsp} and @tomato purée{30%ml}. Stir together and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @water{300%ml}, @coconut milk{200%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Stir to combine.

Add the sweet potato and @red split lentils{100%g} to your pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a simmer, cover with a #lid{} and cook, stirring frequently, until the lentils and sweet potato are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. 5 mins before the dal is ready, add the @king prawns{150%g} and cook.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.
> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

> TIP: If the dal is looking a little dry, just add a splash of water.

== Dukkah Salsa ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Pop the lime zest into a #bowl{} with the @dukkah mix{1%tsp} and coriander. Add the @olive oil for the salsa{1%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice and a pinch of salt and pepper. Mix together and leave to the side.

== Cheat's Chapati ==

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (don't add any oil). When the pan is hot, dry-fry your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} for ~{30%seconds} on each side. You want your tortillas to char slightly, so keep an eye on them. Transfer each tortilla to a #plate{} making a chapati pile (spread each one with a little butter, if you have any). Keep them warm by covering the plate with #foil{}.

== To Serve ==

Once the dal is cooked, stir through the @chopped kale{100%g} to submerge in the sauce and simmer until wilted, ~{4-6%minutes}. Squeeze in a little lime juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper or lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{} with the dukkah salsa on top and the chapatis on the side. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've decided to add prawns to your meal, 5 mins before the dal is ready, add the prawns and cook.